gr.interamerican.bo2.impl.open.records
Class CsvRecord

java.lang.Object
  gr.interamerican.bo2.impl.open.records.AbstractBaseRecord
      gr.interamerican.bo2.impl.open.records.CsvRecord
All Implemented Interfaces:
IndexedFieldsRecord<Integer>, ModifiableIndexedFieldsRecord<Integer>, Record
public class CsvRecord
extends AbstractBaseRecord
implements ModifiableIndexedFieldsRecord<Integer>

CsvRecord is a record of a comma separated values (CSV) file.
The default separator is semicolon, but it is possible to change the separator to any character.
CsvRecords are zero based.

setFields

public void setFields(String[] newFields)
Sets the fields of this CsvRecord. This method will never change this record's count of fields. If this record has more fields than the specified array, elements, then the remaining fields will be filled with blanks. If this record has less fields than the specified array's length, then the remaining elements of the array will be ignored.

Parameters:
newFields - Array with new fields.

setFieldsIgnoreNone

public void setFieldsIgnoreNone(String[] newFields)
Sets all fields of the specified array to be the fields of this CsvRecord. If the length of the specified array, exceeds the count of this record's fields, then this record will increase its fields so that all elements of the specified array fit as fields of this record.

Parameters:
newFields - Array with new fields.
